com.github.gwtd3.api.interpolators

Interface InterpolatorFactory<O>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractInterpolatorFactory, JSNIInterpolatorFactory

    public interface InterpolatorFactory<O>
    Represents an object that can create an Interpolator.

    A factory should return null when no interpolators support the input arguments.

    Author:
    Anthony Schiochet

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject asJSOFunction()
      Return a one-arg JS function wrapping the interpolation.
      <I> Interpolator<O> create(I a, I b)
      Create an interpolator appropriate for interpolating the input value, or return null if the factory does not support the two specified input values.

        Parameters:
